@page "/"
@using SkiaSharp
@using SkiaSharp.Views.Blazor

<div class="top-container">
    <div class="canvas-container">
        <SKCanvasView OnPaintSurface="OnPaintSurface" />
    </div>
</div>

<style>
    .top-container { flex: 1 1 auto; width: 100%; min-height: 100%; border: 1px solid red; padding: 1rem; display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
    .canvas-container { flex: 1; background-color: #90ee90; width: 100%; height: 100%; }
    .canvas-container canvas { padding: 0; margin: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; }
</style>

@code {
    private void OnPaintSurface(SKPaintSurfaceEventArgs e)
    {
        var canvas = e.Surface.Canvas;
        canvas.Clear(SKColors.Blue);
        using var paint = new SKPaint { Color = SKColors.Yellow, IsAntialias = true };
        SKFont font = new SKFont(SKTypeface.Default, 32);
        canvas.DrawText($"{e.RawInfo.Width} : {e.RawInfo.Height}", 20, 50, font, paint);
    }
}

proposedResponse.body:
Thanks for the detailed report and reproduction project!

We've confirmed this issue. The SKCanvasView canvas element does not fill 100% of its parent container height when using flexbox with percentage-based CSS heights. This reproduces across all tested versions:

| Version | Result |
|---------|--------|
| 3.119.0 (reported) | ❌ Reproduced |
| 3.119.2 (latest) | ❌ Reproduced |
| main (source) | ❌ Reproduced |

The root cause is the interaction between the HTML `<canvas>` element's intrinsic sizing and CSS flexbox layout. The SKCanvasView component renders a bare `<canvas>` element (inline by default), and the JS interop sets its HTML `width`/`height` attributes for the drawing buffer resolution, which changes the canvas's intrinsic size and can interfere with flexbox height calculations.

**Workaround:** Set `display:block` and explicit sizing directly on the `SKCanvasView` component:

```razor
<SKCanvasView OnPaintSurface="OnPaintSurface"
    style="width:100%; height:100%; display:block;" />
```

Alternatively, use `position:absolute` to decouple from intrinsic sizing:

```css
.canvas-container {
    position: relative;
    flex: 1;
}
.canvas-container canvas {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0; bottom: 0; left: 0; right: 0;
}
```

See also #2038 and #2834 for prior discussion of this pattern.
